HEADWORD: Quadrel
<hw>Quad"rel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>quadrello</ets>, LL. <ets>quadrellus</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>quadrus</ets> square. See <er>Quadrate</er>, and cf.
<er>Quarrel</er> an arrow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A square piece of
turf or peat.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A square brick, tile, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quadrennial</ent>⟦br⟧
